
[1]encaustic

   ENCAUS'TIC, a. [Gr. caustic, to burn.] Pertaining to the art of
   enameling, and to painting in burnt wax. Encaustic painting, is a
   method in which wax is employed to give a gloss to colors.

   ENCAUS'TIC, n. Enamel or enameling.

   1. The method of painting in burnt wax.
